Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Campus Library Coordinator Penticton , BC Description OKANAGAN COLLEGEOkanagan College transforms lives and communities. We are one of Canada's leading colleges. We create outstanding educational experiences for our learners, both students and employees. We work and learn in a welcoming and caring culture. We are a catalyst for change through collaboration with our learners and partners. We serve, lead and anticipate the social, economic and environmental needs of communities.Position Title:Campus Library CoordinatorCompetition Number:C002542Division/Portfolio:Library ServicesDepartment/Program:LibraryCampus/Centre:PentictonYour Opportunity:Under the limited supervision of the Campus Librarian, the Campus Library Coordinator is responsible for the day-to-day operation of the public area of the Campus Library; provides leadership and direction to the Circulation team to ensure high quality service delivery; develops, recommends and implements policies and procedures; works with the Campus Librarian and other departments to ensure the smooth operation of the campus library; assists library users with library processes and helps defuse and resolve difficult interactions with library users. The Campus Library Coordinator coordinates training and scheduling of support staff, student library pages, and student IT lab monitors.Education and Experience:Completion of a 2-year Library Technician Diploma and an additional 2 years academic post-secondary education are required. A minimum of 4 years’ experience in an academic library is required.Functions and Duties:Coordinates work schedules for support staff and student employees to meet Library operating requirements and service standardsEstablishes work standards and monitors and assesses work output for Library public services areas and responds to and provides direction on issues that require immediate supervisory attention; provides input into support staff evaluations conducted by the Campus LibrarianProvides input for staffing needs and assists with the recruitment process; hires and supervises student pages; trains Library support staff, student IT lab monitors and student library pages; signs student timesheets and ensures support staff timesheets are accurately prepared and submittedWorks with Campus Library Coordinators at other campuses to ensure Library service standards College-wideAssists in difficult service interactions and serves as a resource person to provide advice to staff and library users about policies and procedures (e.g. fines and loans, room bookings, etc.)Identifies changing circumstances that may require the review and revision of current library policies and practices; analyzes, plans, and recommends strategies to increase the efficiency and effectiveness of operations; develops and maintains procedures manuals for circulation staff; communicates as appropriate with the Campus Librarian.Participates with the other Campus Library Coordinators as a member of the Circulation Working Group (CWG) including rotating Chair and recording dutiesResponsible for the receipt and accounting of all monies in the Campus Library public service area including deposits; coordinates weekly ordering, processing and accounting of Pay-Per-Print vouchers with Print ServicesReviews and adjudicates fine appeals, claims returned, missing and damaged items, and accesses college users’ library account for the purpose of clarifying or resolving problems with fines and billings; removes flags from the student registration system and issues clearances; maintains records for billings and finesCoordinates photo ID delivery for students in conjunction with Facilities and Business Services, including payment for replacement cardsCreates and updates information for the campus library website and designs and produces effective and visually appealing communication materials including signageResponsible for coordinating statistics and reports for reference, user education and other public servicesAssists library users, including students, employees and the general public, by telephone, electronically and face-to-face; handles queries in a sensitive and timely manner and refers to the Campus Librarian, other OC departments, or other resources as appropriateHelps library users to locate materials, search for information using the online catalogue, research databases, and web search engines, properly cite sources, use library equipment including microfilm/fiche readers, photocopiers and printers and with routine productivity software and institutional computer accountsCoordinates and assists with operational activities in public services including answering user questions and referring to appropriate resources, opening and closing library facilities as necessary, borrower services activities related to library cards, circulating library materials, intercampus requests; monitors the delivery processes and services supporting circulation; maintains the library reserves systemCarries out collection management activities such as collection inventory and the resolution of periodical holdings discrepancies; identifies and reviews cataloguing, processing and other anomalies; reports discrepanciesEnsures appropriate maintenance of Library public service area facilities, technology and equipment (i.e. laptops, photocopiers, computers) by reporting issues, submitting work requests, and coordinating with the appropriate departmentAccesses the student registration system to confirm student course registration or as otherwise requiredPerforms other duties as assigned.Skills and Abilities:Knowledge of automated library systemsProficiency with MS Office programs, particularly Word and ExcelTechnical aptitude for learning new systems and software and propensity for life-long learning to ensure technical currencyAbility to work effectively with limited supervisionAbility to provide a high level of customer service, to handle user complaints and suggestions, and to resolve conflictMust be flexible and able to manage a high work volume and conflicting priorities in order to meet deadlinesAppointment Type:Support - Regular Full-timeAppointment Start Date:10/16/2023Schedule:Monday through Friday, from 7:30 a.m. to 3:30 p.m.Annual Salary/Hourly Rate:$59,951 - $68,505Special Instructions to Applicants:Shortlisted internal candidates must notify the current Support Staff Bargaining Chairperson and People Services if they want a union observer present during interviews and final selection of candidates.Posting Opening Date:08/31/2023Posting Closing Date:09/17/2023APPLICATIONS:To apply for this position, please go to our employment site: https://www.employmentopportunities.okanagan.bc.ca and complete an on-line application. All applications must be submitted through our employment site to be considered.Okanagan College is committed to increasing the equitable and inclusive participation of marginalized people in all aspects of college life. We welcome and encourage applications from Indigenous Peoples, Black People, members of racialized groups/visible minorities, people with disabilities and people with diverse gender identities or expressions. People with disabilities who anticipate needing accommodations for any part of the application process may contact, in confidence, AccessibilityHR@okanagan.bc.ca Compensation $59,951 - $68,505 Closes: 17 September, 2023 Okanagan College Penticton , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
