 of vacation or illness;Attends departmental staff meetings;Assists with the maintenance of library collections by selecting, organizing and weeding materials as required;Prepares reading lists, guides and other finding aids in print and digitally;Communicates with customers through a variety of media;Reads professional journals and participates in professional activities such as conferences and committees as required;Catalogues and classifies library materials;Performs related duties as assigned. SALARY RATE AND RANGE: $37.10/hr to $40.57/hr (2023 rates) APPLICATION DEADLINE: 4:00 pm, September 11, 2023 This is a bargaining unit position, CUPE Local 1146-Library Unit. Library Unit employees will first be given consideration for this vacancy followed by other applicants. Interested persons are requested to submit a cover letter and resume to: Lori Peixoto Administrative Assistant Woodstock Public Library 445 Hunter Street Woodstock ON N4S 4G7 lpeixoto@mywpl.ca Personal information is collected in accordance with the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Personal Privacy Act. The Woodstock Public Library Board is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. Accommodations are available for all parts of the recruitment process. Applicants need to make their needs known in advance. Compensation 37.10/hr to 40.57/hr Closes: 11 September, 2023 Woodstock Public Library Woodstock , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
