on of displays. Information and Reference Services (20%) • Provide information and reference services using print and electronic tools. • Instruct library users in the use of online catalogue, online databases, reference materials, and the internet. • Assist with the preparation of web-based information literacy tools and guides to support the curriculum. Acquisitions (15%) • Assist in developing and processing acquisition lists. • Assist with claims for library materials that have not been received or where there are errors. • Perform other related tasks as assigned. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Must have a diploma (DEC) in Information and Library Technologies or equivalent. Fluency in English (spoken, written and comprehension). ADDITIONAL QUALIFICATIONS Demonstrated knowledge in the use of various online databases, automated library systems (i.e. Koha), and related searching tools and techniques. Knowledge in the use of RDA cataloguing standards, with an understanding of new and emerging trends in bibliographic description. Knowledge of the RDA Toolkit will be considered an asset. Recent experience and expertise applying Library of Congress Classification and Subject Headings; knowledge of Classification Web will be considered an asset. Knowledge of and experience using LibApps (e.g. LibGuides, LibCal, etc.) is a strong asset. Experience providing research and reference services to a diverse client base. Experience in an academic setting will be considered an asset. Familiarity with document preservation and archival standards. Must possess excellent communication, organizational and interpersonal skills. Must have excellent analytical and problem-solving skills. Must be diligent, dynamic, creative and detail oriented. Must be able to work independently with minimal supervision, and have the ability to work as part of a team. Must be able to work effectively with respect to deadlines and produce accurate results. Must be flexible and able to adapt quickly to different situations. Must have excellent customer service skills. Must have a strong work ethic and exercise discretion. Interested candidates should submit their résumé, along with appropriate documentation ONLINE on our college website in the career page at http://www.cegep-heritage.qc.ca/manitou/. Click on the job posting, then click on "APPLY". You will be able to create an account and upload your resume and cover letter. Please note that only online applications will be considered. N.B.: Candidates may be required to submit to selection tests. Only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted. Cégep Heritage College applies an Equal Access program and encourages women, Indigenous peoples, members of visible and ethnic minorities, and persons with a disability to apply. Compensation $23.82 to $30.82 Closes: 10 September, 2023 Cegep Heritage College Gatineau , QC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
