m an accredited post-secondary institution with a focus in education, technology, digital media, design, or related field or an equivalent combination of education and experience to the satisfaction of the Library CEO. Minimum of two years of relevant public service experience. Proficiency with software applications and operating systems (such as: Microsoft Windows 10/11 and Office 365, MacOS and iOS, Adobe Creative Cloud, digital audio workstations, electronic library databases and related software/web services and additional applications and services as they become available). Proficiency with hardware technologies (such as: desktop/laptop/tablet computers, projectors, digital cameras and audio recording hardware, laser printers and 3D printers, virtual reality, and additional hardware technologies and services as they become available). Strong ability to facilitate digital literacy programs and services to members of all ages and internal staff in both individual and group settings, such as web development, audio/visual/3D design, computer/tablet/mobile skills, and productivity suite skills. Willingness to take initiative, demonstrate strong problem-solving skills and to continually learn new things on the job. Experience in providing in-depth reference, reader advisory, and circulation services. Excellent interpersonal and communication skills. Ability to work collaboratively and independently in an environment of constant change. Valid First Aid Certification is considered an asset. A satisfactory Standard Criminal Record Check (CPIC) is required prior to commencement of employment.Application:The Clarington Public Library, Museums, and Archives value diversity, equity, and inclusion within its community and workplace. We welcome applications from individuals of diverse backgrounds. Please submit your cover letter and resume in Word or PDF format by Monday, September 11th, 2023 to the following confidential email address: resumes@clarington-library.on.ca quoting the job title and file number 2023-CPL15AF.We thank all applicants for their interest; however, only those under consideration will be contacted. Personal Information is collected in accordance with the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Personal Privacy Act and will only be used for candidate selection.We are pleased to accommodate individual needs in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act, 2005, throughout our recruitment process. If you require accommodation at any time, please contact Human Resources. Compensation $26.25 to $32.37 per hour (CUPE Grade 4) Closes: 11 September, 2023 Clarington Public Library, Museums, and Archives Bowmanville , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
