s with irregular breaksSome element of personal risk involved in the performance of these duties Minimum Qualifications: Library Technician diploma plus one to three years of library experience preferredMinimum one course in Cataloguing Library Material required Conditions of Employment: Must be legally entitled to work in CanadaMust provide a satisfactory Criminal Record Check and clear Vulnerable Sector Check prior to employmentMinimum Class “G2” Ontario Driver’s License (or equivalent) is preferred Please submit all cover letters and resumes for this position to Richard Bee, CEO, before 4:00 PM CST on Friday, September 8. Application packages can be emailed to rbee@ffpltc.ca or dropped off at the Fort Frances Public Library Technology Centre during open hours. Please note that only candidates selected for interview will be contacted. Compensation $26.13/hr - $32.64/hr Closes: 8 September, 2023 Fort Frances Public Library Technology Centre Fort Frances , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
