Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Librarian Liaison - Temporary Assignment (August 2023 - May 2024) Hamilton , ON Description Status: Temporary Assignment (July 2023 – May 2024)Home Campus: FennellHours: Monday to FridayRate of Pay: Commensurate upon qualifications and experiencePay band: Not applicablePosting Date: July 13th, 2023Closing Date: September 8th, 2023 at 7:00pm ESTPlease apply online at: www.mohawkcollege.ca/careersWe support and encourage the contributions of our diverse employees. We are committed to nurturing an equitable, diverse and inclusive (EDI) environment for everyone who learns and works at Mohawk College. We believe the rich diversity among our students and the communities we serve should be reflected within our workforce. As educators we believe it is important to act and show leadership in advancing the principles of equity, diversity and inclusion in our community.Mohawk College is currently recruiting for our nextLibrarian LiaisonWorking collaboratively with a team, the Librarian Liaison role will contribute to faculty liaison, information literacy instruction and information services. The Librarian Liaison will support liaison services in one or more programs, supporting faculty with class instruction, research, resource curation and related supports. This will also act as lead on the Library Team for Indigenous-related initiatives and outreach, and Information Services development and assessment.RESPONSIBILITIES:The duties of this position will include, but are not limited to the following:Support faculty through class instruction, resource curation, assignment/ course support in liaison area.Evaluate resources and curate collections to support liaison program of study; work collaboratively with team to develop LibGuides and related resources.Support new program/course development at all levels (continuing education, graduate certificate, diploma and degree) within liaison area.Act as Lead in the Library for Indigenous-related initiatives and outreach, ensuring services and collections are accessible to Indigenous learners.Represent the library on provincial library Indigenous education-related committees and communicate updates to library team through training webinars, workshops and communication channels.Keep up-to-date on trends and issues and communicate to library staff about supports and resources.Ensure information services are accessible to Indigenous students.Liaise with other areas of the college offering related services.Support the Information Services team through training, development and assessment of services.Develop measures to assess service across all information service channels (e.g., in-person, chat, email, reference by appointment, etc.) and all campuses ensuring services are accessible, equitable and inclusive to the entire Mohawk College community.Seek innovative ways to improve and innovate service working collaboratively with the team across all campuses.Provide ongoing training and one-on-one support to the Information Services team to improve service and increase confidence.Monitor and evaluate emerging information service and UX trends and technology in academic libraries and communicate trends to library team.QUALIFICATIONS:The successful applicant must have:Masters of Library and Information Sciences or equivalent degree from an ALA accredited program.Minimum of 3-5 years of related library work as a librarian, ideally in an academic setting.Strong understanding of core library practices and emerging trends in information service, instruction, collections, digital initiatives, research support.Familiarity with learning management systems (i.e. Canvas).Working knowledge of library systems (i.e. Alma).Commitment to EDI, decolonization of library practices, accessibility and sustainability through a proven track record of human-centered library assessment.Sound knowledge of cataloging practices and principles.Excellent customer service and interpersonal skills.Ability to work in a team environment through initiative, flexibility and adaptability.Demonstrate ability to multi-task and meet the demands of a changing work environment.Show strong problem solving and critical thinking skills.Demonstrated ability to design and deliver training in an academic environment.Excellent presentation skills.Experience evaluating and delivering public service with a strong service-centered philosophy.Knowledge of user experience (UX) trends and developments as they relate to library reference and information service work.Ability to work well in a collegial environment.The successful candidate must have an ability to relate theoretical knowledge and practical applications through innovative delivery methods so as to provide a meaningful learning environment for students of diverse backgrounds and ages. The ability to work as a part of a team and demonstration of excellent interpersonal and communication skills are essential.Faculty members hired at Mohawk College must be prepared to teach with a learner-centered approach and to assist in the development and application of alternate delivery methods. May be assigned to teach classes at any College Campus.Mohawk College prioritizes recruiting and retaining diverse employees. With this in mind, the College is committed to fostering inclusive and barrier-free recruitment and selection processes.Should you require accommodation through any stage of the recruitment process, please contact the Human Resources Department at (905) 575 - 2047.Mohawk College is strongly committed to diversity within its community and especially welcomes applications from racialized persons, women, Indigenous people, persons with disabilities, 2SLGBTQIA+ persons, and others who may contribute to the further diversification of ideas.For more information concerning the Mohawk College strategic plan, please see: strategicplan.mohawkcollege.ca/ Compensation Competitive compensation commensurate with experience; the salary range for this position begins at $67,000 Closes: 8 September, 2023 Mohawk College Hamilton , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
